3.4.1.4.3.1\" class=\"ltx_td ltx_align_center ltx_border_t\"><span id=\"S4.T3.4.1.4.3.1.1\" class=\"ltx_text\" style=\"font-size:90%;\">HAR</span></td>\n<td id=\"S4.T3.4.1.4.3.2\" class=\"ltx_td ltx_align_center ltx_border_t\"><span id=\"S4.T3.4.1.4.3.2.1\" class=\"ltx_text\" style=\"font-size:90%;\">87.6%</span></td>\n<td id=\"S4.T3.4.1.4.3.3\" class=\"ltx_td ltx_align_center ltx_border_t\"><span id=\"S4.T3.4.1.4.3.3.1\" class=\"ltx_text\" style=\"font-size:90%;\">89.3%</span></td>\n</tr>\n<tr id=\"S4.T3.4.1.5.4\" class=\"ltx_tr\">\n<td id=\"S4.T3.4.1.5.4.1\" class=\"ltx_td ltx_align_center ltx_border_bb ltx_border_t\"><span id=\"S4.T3.4.1.5.4.1.1\" class=\"ltx_text\" style=\"font-size:90%;\">ID</span></td>\n<td id=\"S4.T3.4.1.5.4.2\" class=\"ltx_td ltx_align_center ltx_border_bb ltx_border_t\"><span id=\"S4.T3.4.1.5.4.2.1\" class=\"ltx_text\" style=\"font-size:90%;\">59.3%</span></td>\n<td id=\"S4.T3.4.1.5.4.3\" class=\"ltx_td ltx_align_center ltx_border_bb ltx_border_t\"><span id=\"S4.T3.4.1.5.4.3.1\" class=\"ltx_text\" style=\"font-size:90%;\">59.4%</span></td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n\n",
        "footnotes": "",
        "references": [
            "To investigate whether the ES mechanism will cause undesirable accuracy loss, we compare the final accuracy/negative perplexity of FLrce and FLrce without early stopping (FLrce w/o ES). The only difference between FLrce and FLrce w/o ES is that the latter ignores the ES criterion and keeps training until reaching the maximum global iteration. Note that the relationship-based client selection strategy still applies. As Table 3 shows, the ES mechanism does not cause too much loss of accuracy/negative perplexity. On the worst case, the ES mechanism degrades the final accuracy by 8.8% (IC). However, the ES mechanism reduces almost 80% training rounds (101 vs. 500). Besides, FLrce still outperforms the baselines for IC even with the accuracy deduction (see Table 2).",
            "The result in Table 3 empirically proves the validity of our hypothesis in subsection 3.3. We plan to find further theoretical analysis to support our hypothesis in the future."
